    <a href="#resources">Resources</a>
    <a href="/Engineering/CSE/cse.ejs">Go Back</a>
  </div>
  
  <header>
    <h1>DevOps</h1>
    <p>Master the art of DevOps with comprehensive guides on tools, practices, and automation techniques.</p>
  </header>
  
  <section id="fundamentals">
    <h2 class="section-title">DevOps Fundamentals</h2>
    <div class="tech-grid">
      <div class="tech-card">
        <h3>What is DevOps?</h3>
        <p>Understand the culture, practices, and tools that combine software development (Dev) with IT operations (Ops).</p>
        <a href="https://aws.amazon.com/devops/what-is-devops/" class="learn-btn" target="_blank">Learn More</a>
      </div>
      
      <div class="tech-card">
        <h3>CI/CD</h3>
        <p>Learn about Continuous Integration and Continuous Deployment/Delivery pipelines and their importance.</p>
        <a href="https://www.atlassian.com/continuous-delivery/principles" class="learn-btn" target="_blank">Learn More</a>
      </div>
      
      <div class="tech-card">
        <h3>Infrastructure as Code</h3>
        <p>Discover how to manage and provision infrastructure through code using tools like Terraform and Ansible.</p>
        <a href="https://www.hashicorp.com/resources/what-is-infrastructure-as-code" class="learn-btn" target="_blank">Learn More</a>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>
  
  <section id="tools">
    <h2 class="section-title">Essential DevOps Tools</h2>
    <div class="tech-grid">
      <div class="tech-card">
        <h3>Version Control</h3>
        <p>Git and GitHub for source code management and collaboration.</p>
        <a href="https://git-scm.com/book/en/v2" class="learn-btn" target="_blank">Learn Git</a>
      </div>
      
      <div class="tech-card">
        <h3>Containerization</h3>
        <p>Docker and Kubernetes for container management and orchestration.</p>
        <a href="https://www.docker.com/get-started" class="learn-btn" target="_blank">Start Docker</a>
      </div>
      
      <div class="tech-card">
        <h3>CI/CD Tools</h3>
        <p>Jenkins, GitLab CI, and GitHub Actions for automated pipelines.</p>
        <a href="https://www.jenkins.io/doc/tutorials/" class="learn-btn" target="_blank">Jenkins Tutorials</a>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section id="practices">
    <h2 class="section-title">DevOps Best Practices</h2>
    <div class="tech-grid">
      <div class="tech-card">
        <h3>1. Version Control Everything</h3>
        <p>Use Git or other version control systems to track changes in code, configuration, and infrastructure.</p>
        <a href="https://git-scm.com/book/en/v2" class="learn-btn" target="_blank">Learn Git</a>
      </div>
  
      <div class="tech-card">
        <h3>2. Automate Everything</h3>
        <p>Automate repetitive tasks like testing, deployment, and infrastructure provisioning to save time and reduce errors.</p>
        <a href="https://www.redhat.com/en/topics/automation" class="learn-btn" target="_blank">Learn More</a>
      </div>
  
      <div class="tech-card">
        <h3>3. Continuous Integration/Continuous Deployment (CI/CD)</h3>
        <p>Implement CI/CD pipelines to ensure faster and more reliable software delivery.</p>
        <a href="https://www.atlassian.com/continuous-delivery/principles" class="learn-btn" target="_blank">Learn CI/CD</a>
      </div>
  
      <div class="tech-card">
        <h3>4. Infrastructure as Code (IaC)</h3>
        <p>Use tools like Terraform and Ansible to manage infrastructure as code for consistency and scalability.</p>
        <a href="https://www.hashicorp.com/resources/what-is-infrastructure-as-code" class="learn-btn" target="_blank">Learn IaC</a>
      </div>
  
      <div class="tech-card">
        <h3>5. Monitor and Log Everything</h3>
        <p>Use tools like Prometheus, Grafana, and ELK Stack to monitor and log system performance and errors.</p>
        <a href="https://prometheus.io/docs/introduction/overview/" class="learn-btn" target="_blank">Learn Monitoring</a>
      </div>
  
      <div class="tech-card">
        <h3>6. Security as Code</h3>
        <p>Integrate security practices into the DevOps pipeline to ensure secure software delivery.</p>
        <a href="https://owasp.org/www-project-devsecops-guideline/" class="learn-btn" target="_blank">Learn DevSecOps</a>
      </div>
  
      <div class="tech-card">
        <h3>7. Collaboration and Communication</h3>
        <p>Foster a culture of collaboration between development, operations, and other teams to achieve shared goals.</p>
        <a href="https://www.atlassian.com/devops/culture" class="learn-btn" target="_blank">Learn More</a>
      </div>
  
      <div class="tech-card">
        <h3>8. Feedback Loops</h3>
        <p>Implement feedback loops to continuously improve processes and address issues proactively.</p>
        <a href="https://www.thoughtworks.com/insights/blog/feedback-loops-devops" class="learn-btn" target="_blank">Learn Feedback Loops</a>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>
  
  <section id="roadmap">
    <h2 class="section-title">DevOps Learning Roadmap</h2>
    <div class="roadmap">
      <div class="roadmap-step">
        <h3>1. Programming Basics</h3>
        <p>Learn a scripting language (Python, Shell) and version control with Git.</p>
      </div>
      
      <div class="roadmap-step">
        <h3>2. Linux & Networking</h3>
        <p>Master Linux administration and networking fundamentals.</p>
      </div>
      
      <div class="roadmap-step">
        <h3>3. Containerization</h3>
        <p>Learn Docker and container orchestration with Kubernetes.</p>
      </div>
      
      <div class="roadmap-step">
        <h3>4. CI/CD</h3>
        <p>Implement continuous integration and deployment pipelines.</p>
      </div>
      
      <div class="roadmap-step">
        <h3>5. Infrastructure as Code</h3>
        <p>Master infrastructure automation with Terraform and configuration management.</p>
      </div>
      
      <div class="roadmap-step">
        <h3>6. Monitoring & Logging</h3>
        <p>Learn tools like Prometheus, Grafana, and ELK Stack.</p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>
  
  <section id="resources">
    <h2 class="section-title">Learning Resources</h2>
    <div class="resource-grid">
      <div class="channel-card">
        <h4>TechWorld with Nana</h4>
        <p>Comprehensive DevOps tutorials and real-world examples.</p>
        <a href="https://www.youtube.com/@TechWorldwithNana" class="channel-link" target="_blank">Visit Channel →</a>
      </div>
      
      <div class="channel-card">
        <h4>DevOps Toolkit</h4>
        <p>Advanced DevOps practices and tools demonstrations.</p>
        <a href="https://www.youtube.com/@DevOpsToolkit" class="channel-link" target="_blank">Visit Channel →</a>
      </div>
      
      <div class="channel-card">
        <h4>KodeKloud</h4>
        <p>Hands-on DevOps training and certification preparation.</p>
        <a href="https://www.youtube.com/@KodeKloud" class="channel-link" target="_blank">Visit Channel →</a>
      </div>
      
      <div class="channel-card">
        <h4>DevOps Journey</h4>
        <p>Step-by-step guides for DevOps tools and practices.</p>
        <a href="https://www.youtube.com/@DevOpsJourney" class="channel-link" target="_blank">Visit Channel →</a>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>
  
</body>
